ExperienceSummary.Description: ~~~~~~~~~   is experienced in:  Information Technology (User Interface); and User Experience.    ~~~~~~~~~   has 6 years of work experience.

Positions.Description:
Working in an agile environment on multiple, simultaneous desktop and mobile iOS,
Android products, designing features and common experiences, defining new
patterns and paradigms, along with creation of UI components and assets.

• Lead projects through iterative lifecycle of research - design - development - testing.
• Create role and task models, personas, user flows and scenarios to define and bring
clarity to user and client needs.

• Communicate design decisions to stakeholders through mid-hi-fi wireframes and detailed interaction specifications.

• Rapidly build prototypes, design mobile & web UI and work closely with developers
to implement designs.

Participated in user research and research consolidation; identified opportunities
from the research that balanced the needs of the users with the needs of the client.

• Developed personas that represented users and helped focus designs.
• Defined the scope and navigational flow of applications.

• Created interactive medium fidelity prototypes and evaluated the visual design of the final product mock-ups for the client.

Delivered high-fidelity user interface designs for web, designed site branding,

creation of illustrations and animations, defining client specific style guides and generated design assets. Produced logos, business cards and promotional materials.

Achievements: September 2015 - June 2017   design and brand identity, Motion design, Compositing
